directions.Direction: Cut the top off of a head of garlic then generously drizzle with olive oil and season. Add a sprig of thyme on top.
Tightly wrap in foil and bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.
Peel about 10-12 medium-small yellow potatoes. Once peeled, evenly cut in half.
Add the peeled potatoes to a bowl of cold water and set aside.
Heat a large pot of water to boil and generously salt.
Once boiling add in the potatoes and boil until fork tender. Roughly 30 minutes.
In the meantime, grab a small pot/ sauce pan and add in milk, cream, and herbs.
Heat to medium heat and lightly simmer until fragrant, about 10 minutes. Once done, remove from heat and set aside.
Once the potatoes are fork tender, strain and add back to the pot.
Add in butter ,sour cream, and squeeze in the roasted garlic then use a masher or hand mixer to break down the potatoes before mixing.
Slowly pour in the warm cream mixture while mixing with the hand mixer.
Once smooth to the desired consistency, stop mixing and season. Use a spatula to gently fold in and add in another tablespoon of butter.
Add to desired serving dish and garnish with dried parsley flakes and a few pads of butter.
Serve and enjoy!
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
Bring a large pot of equal parts water and chicken stock to boil. Add in a few teaspoons of salt. Cook until al dente, 6 minutes.
Drain noodles, then stir in butter and black pepper. Then set aside.
While the noodles are boiling, shred all of the cheese. Be mindful that some will be used for the topping and there may be excess cheese.
Keep roughly 3 cups of cheese for the sauce, 1 1/2 cups for the inner layer, and 2 cups for the topping.
Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat. Add in shallots and garlic, and saute until fragrant (2 minutes).
Slowly stir in flour, 1 tbsp at a time, to create a roux.
Stir until flour is fully cooked down, about 2 minutes. Then slowly stir in milk and heavy cream with a whisk to break down the flour.
Add in 3/4 a block of cream cheese, then stir until fully melted.
Stir in spices then bring sauce to a simmer.
Once the sauce is bubbling, reduce heat to low then slowly stir in each cheese, about 1/2 cup at a time.
Once the sauce is velvety and fully melted, remove from heat.

Add 2 cups of the cooked pasta to a 9x13 baking dish. Then pour over 1/2 cup of the cheese sauce on top and sprinkle in roughly 1/2 cup of cheese. Mix until noodles and sauce is well incorporated. Repeat this step.

Smooth noodles out, then drizzle with an additional 1/4 cup of cheese sauce, then top with roughly 1 1/2 cup of all of the different cheeses for the final layer. (Note: there will be remaining cheese sauce).
For an extra cheesy crust, add small pieces of mozzarella on top.
Sprinkle with cajun seasoning and dried parsley (optional).
Bake for 40 minutes or until the top layer is golden and bubbly. Broil for 2-3 minutes for an extra golden crust (optional).
Remove from the oven and let stand for at least 10 minutes before serving.
Now serve and enjoy!
Once yams are peeled, slice into even 1/2 inch thick rounds.
In a medium pot over medium-high heat, melt down butter then add the listed ingredients and stir together until well combined.
Note: I had over 5 cups of sliced yams, and my pot was too small, so I doubled this recipe and made a total of 2 brown sugar sauces.
Once the sauce is slightly simmering, evenly layer in as many yams as can fit, then cover and allow to simmer for about 7 minutes or until fork tender, but not falling apart.
Preheat oven to 375 F degrees.
Evenly layer yams in a baking dish, then drizzle extra brown sugar sauce over top.
Tightly cover with foil, then bake for about 45 minutes or until yams are soft and almost fall apart.
Once nice and soft, remove from the oven, serve warm and enjoy!
Heat a large wok or frying pan over medium-low heat. Add in oil and butter.
Once melted, add in garlic. Stir then let sit untouched for 2-3 minutes until golden.
Then stir in rice. Increase stove to medium-high heat.
Season the rice with the listed spices and mix. Then leave untouched for 3 minutes.
Stir in butter, then cook for an additional 5 minutes until rice beings to crisp.
Remove from heat and pair with your favorite main dishes or top with a fried egg and green onions for a savory breakfast! Enjoy!
In a small bowl combine yeast, sugar, and warm water. Gently stir and cover. Allow yeast to proof for 10 minutes.
In a separate large bowl whisk together dry ingredients.
Then pour in proofed yeast mixture, yogurt, milk, and oil into dry mixture. Mix with a spatula until well combined.
Then use hands to bring dough together and lightly kneed until a soft ball forms. Add more flour as needed if the dough is too wet/sticky.
Once the dough becomes a nice ball, add to a lightly greased large bowl. Then cover with a tea towel and rest over kitchen light or natural light.
Allow dough to proof for an hour or until doubled in size.
Now add dough ball to a lightly floured surface, then slightly stretch out into an oval. Cut dough into 8ths.
Then using the palm of your hands, gently roll each piece of dough into a ball and set onto a parchment lined tray.
Begin heating a large cast iron pan over medium-high heat.
Using a rolling pin or your hands, gently roll each dough ball into an oval shape or your desired naan shape. Thickness or thinness dependent on naan preference.
Your pan should be smoking before adding the rolled out naan pieces. Add a small drizzle of oil, 1/2 tsp then lay naan down away from you.
Brush the top side with oil and once many bubbles begin to form, flip over and allow to cook for about 1-2 minutes or so.
Then repeat until all of the naan is done.
Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Cut bottom off of potatoes then use 2 chopsticks to cut slits into each potato, making sure not to cut all the way through.
Drizzle the potatoes with olive oil, and generously salt and pepper. Massage potatoes until well coated.
Place into a baking dish and bake for 40 minutes.
Combine softened butter, herbs, garlic, and 1 tsp of each spice in a small bowl. Mix until well combined.
Add to plastic wrap and roll into log, freeze or refrigerate until hardened.
After 40 minutes, remove potatoes and add slithers of the compound butter into each layer. Then bake for an additional 20-25 minutes until golden brown and crisp.
Garnish with any toppings, I chose sour cream, cheddar cheese, and chives.
Serve and enjoy!
In a large pot, drizzle in oil then add onion and garlic. Sautee over medium heat until translucent.
Then add in the smoked turkey.
Add in chicken stock, water, bouillon paste, vinegar, and plenty of spices.
Cover and allow to simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.
Prep collards by removing the center stem. Cut the leaves in half then stack on top of each other, roll and cut into 2 inch bundles/ spirals.
Place the bundles of collard greens in a mixture of cold water, 1.4 cup white vinegar, 2 tbsp salt, and 2 tsp baking soda.
Soak for 30 minutes then rinse until water runs clear.
After an hour, add the clean and cut greens to the pot then season again.
Cover greens and simmer on medium-low heat for 90 minutes. Remove the smoked turkey and shred, then add back into the greens.
Taste and adjust for salt then remove from heat and serve.
These pair great with hot sauce on top and fresh cornbread on the side!
Butterfly all 3 chicken breasts then generously season both sides with the listed ingredients then set aside to marinate while prepping the other ingredients.
Finely dice onion and jalapeño, making sure to remove the seeds to modify the spice level. Set aside.
Heat oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Then add the seasoned chicken cutlets and cook for 4-5 minutes each side in 2 batches. Cook only 70-80% through.
Once all the chicken is cooked, remove and set aside. Reduce heat to medium. Melt down 2-3 tbsp of butter and add the onions and jalapeños. Sauté for 1 minute, then add garlic and sauté for two.
Add in green chilis and saute for an additional 1 minute.
Slowly stir in flour to create a roux. Mix until all flour is well incorporated and fully cooked, 2-3 minutes.
Use a whisk to slowly add in the chicken broth and break apart clumps of flour.
Stir in the strained and rinsed beans and the strained corn.
Add in the chili seasoning (3/4 of the packet) then cover the chili and allow to simmer for 15-20 minutes.
While the chili simmers, use 2 forks or a hand mixer to gently shred the cooked chicken breast.
Stir in chicken, cream cheese, heavy cream, and season to taste. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and allow to simmer for an additional 15-20 or until thickened to liking.
(Optional) Use a masher or immersion blender to mash up beans and thicken the chili more.
Once done, remove from heat and sprinkle some cilantro over top, then serve and enjoy.
Garnish with tortilla strips, fresh lime, cilantro, sour cream, and even cheese. Enjoy!

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: White Bean Chile & Lime Chicken Chili

directions.Direction: Drizzle chicken breast with olive oil, then generously season both sides with the listed spices.
Allow the chicken to marinade while prepping and chopping the other ingredients.
Heat a large soup pot to medium-high heat then add olive oil and cook the seasoned chicken until blackened. About 4 minutes on each side.
Once all the chicken is cooked, remove from the pot and set aside.
To the same pot, add butter and the diced veggies then sauté for 3 minutes. Then add in the garlic and ginger, and sauté for an additional 1 minute. Sprinkle in some oregano.
Melt in additional butter and then slowly stir in flour to create a roux. Cook the flour down for 2 minutes.
Stir in bone broth and chicken stock with a whisk to break down chunks of flour.
Stir in half & half and then add in the listed fresh herbs. Then cover and bring to a simmer, about 8-10 minutes.
While the soup is simmering, cube up the cooked chicken into bite-sized cubes and add it back to the soup.
Add in the pasta, chopped spinach, kale, and more chicken stock, and then season to taste.
Cover and allow the soup to simmer for 15-20 minutes.
Then remove the lid, take out the herb stems, squeeze in fresh lemon juice then finish with fresh parsley, heavy cream, and additional seasoning (optional).
Serve with fresh, warm bread, and enjoy!
To a small bowl combine the listed ingredients and mix well. Adjust to desired preference.
Remove membrane from the ribs, trim excess fat and clean with cold water, lime juice and white vinegar.
Generously lather all sides of the ribs with mustard.
Once all sides are coated, season generously until the ribs are covered in seasoning.
Preheat the oven to 275 degrees Fahrenheit.
Place ribs on wire rack and baked for 2.5 hours uncovered.
Lay out a large piece of foil the length of the rack of ribs. Use more foil as needed.

Remove ribs from the oven after 2.5 hours. Place butter, 2 tbsp of brown sugar and maple syrup on the bottom of the foil. Place ribs on top of the butter and add additional maple syrup and brown sugar.
Add additional foil if needed and pour in the chicken stock then tightly wrap the ribs.
Place ribs back into the oven for an additional 2 hours.
On a stove top, warm up 1/2 cup of barbecue sauce.

Remove the ribs from the oven and the foil, then place back onto the wire rack. Generously lather with the warm barbecue sauce and sprinkle 1-2 tbsp brown sugar on top. Bake for an additional 10-15 minutes.
Lastly, remove the ribs from the oven, allow to cool, then cut into single ribs and serve.
Preheat oven to 400 F. Rinse and scrub potatoes thoroughly. Poke holes all over the potatoes with a fork or knife. Sprinkle salt on the potatoes and bake until soft, about 1 hour.

Cut lengthwise slits into the potatoes and scoop out flesh into a small bowl. Add butter, sour cream, 1/2 cup each of pepper jack and cheddar cheese, all of your seasonings, and mix well. (Do not over mix being sure to maintain some potato chunks.)
Add filling back into your potatoes and top with a mixture of pepper jack and cheddar cheese and bacon bits. Broil on 450 F for 2-3 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Remove from the oven and top with scallions, serve warm and enjoy.

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: Loaded Baked Potatoes
Description: The Best Loaded Baked Potatoes Recipe

directions.Direction: Optional: remove skin from the salmon. Hot water works well to remove the skin.
Cut the salmon into portioned filets.
To a small bowl, combine spices, lemon juice, and olive oil. Mix until well combined.
Brush the marinade on all sides of the salmon filets. Then refrigerate.
Mince 3-5 garlic cloves. Set aside.
Heat a cast iron skillet to medium-high heat and add 1 tbsp butter, and a drizzle of olive oil.
Sear both sides of the salmon for 3-5 minutes or until crispy and golden.
Once all the salmon is cooked, set aside.
In the same pan or a different one, heat it to medium, and add 1-2 tbsp of butter, and the minced garlic.
Cook garlic until slightly brown and toasted.
Add in the honey, seasonings, 1 tsp of parsley, 2-3 lemon slices, and the cooked salmon.
Remove from heat and bast the honey sauce onto the salmon.
Top with additional parsley (optional).
Serve with your favorite sides, I roasted asparagus and sweet potato.

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: Honey Garlic Chipotle Salmon
Description: The best Honey Garlic Chipotle Salmon Recipe

directions.Direction: With a sharp knife, slit 3-4 inch deep pockets at the top of the chicken.
Place the breast on a cutting board and in a small bowl combine the last 7 ingredients.
Drizzle olive oil onto the chicken breast and add the spice blend to the chicken. Be sure to set aside 1-2 tbsp of the spice blend.
Make sure all sides of the chicken, including the inside are fully coated.
Cover marinated chicken and refrigerate for 20-30 minutes.
In a saucepan, heat to medium-high and add 2 tbsp of butter, 1  tbsp of minced garlic and the chopped spinach.
Add salt and pepper, cook for 5 minutes or until spinach shrinks. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine cooked spinach, cream cheese, 2-3 tbsp of roasted garlic, thyme, sage, rosemary, the  remaining spice blend, cheese, and then mix until well combined.
Remove chicken breast from the refrigerator.
Place your spinach mixture into a piping or ziplock bag with a small slit and pipe into the seasoned chicken breast.
Heat a cast iron skillet to medium-high heat with 1-2 tbsp olive oil and butter.
Once the pan begins to slightly smoke, sear both sides of the chicken breast for 3-5 minutes or until charred/ blackened.
Once seared, remove from heat and add 4-7 small knobs of butter onto the chicken.
(Optional) Sprinkle additional parmesan cheese onto the chicken breast.
Place into the oven on 400 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until the chicken is fully cooked.
Remove from the oven and serve with any sides you like! I made dirty rice and steamed broccoli.
Enjoy!

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: Cajun Stuffed Chicken Breast
Description: The Best Cajun Stuffed Chicken Breast Recipe

ingredients.Name: land o’ lakes garlic herb spread
of Jordan Ramsy’s Garlic Herb Ranch (Recipe available for purchase or on my Instagram)

directions.Direction: Add the chicken tenders to a bowl. Add about 2 tbsp of the spice blend, the buttermilk, and hot sauce. Mix until well combined.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Heat a large deep frying pan with frying oil to 350 degrees.
Add flour, cornstarch, baking powder, and 1 tbsp of the spice blend to a shallow bowl.
Mix until well combined.
Add the tenders to the flour mixture, then back into the buttermilk, and ending in the flour. Let rest on a rack for 10-20 minutes.
Fry the tenders for 10-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Place on paper towels once done.
Melt 1-2 tbsp of garlic spread in a pan on medium high heat. Toast both sides of the brioche buns.
Place toasted bun on a plate, add 1 tbsp of ranch, a piece of lettuce, the chicken tenders, and more ranch if you’d like.
Enjoy!

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: Crispy Chicken Ranch Sandwich
Description: The best Crispy Chicken Ranch Sandwich Recipe

ingredients.Name: each: salt, pepper, garlic powder, and garlic herb seasoning (salt free)

directions.Direction: Cut cauliflower into florets and steam for 10 minutes until soft.
Add steamed cauliflower to a food processor and blend until smooth.
Remove the cauliflower from the food processor and add to a bowl.
To the blended cauliflower combine the last 5 ingredients and mix until well combined and smooth.
Enjoy!

Name: Garlic Herb Cauliflower Mash
Description: The BestGarlic Herb Cauliflower Mash Recipe

directions.Direction: Combine pepper and honey garlic seasoning in a small bowl. Generously add to both sides of the chicken thighs.
Heat a large skillet to high heat. Add olive oil. Sear both sides of the chicken until charred/ blackened. About 3 minutes per side.
Once all the chicken is cooked. Allow to cool, then cut into even chunks/ cubes. Set aside.
Heat a medium skillet to medium heat. Add olive oil and the listed ingredients. Sautee for 1-2 minutes.
Add the bourbon sauce, water, and cornstarch slurry. Mix well. Then add in chicken, stir and cover. Simmer for 15-25 minutes.
Serve with your favorite sides, garnish with green onions and enjoy!
Cut chicken tenders into small pieces or chunks then add to a medium-sized bowl with the listed ingredients. Mix and set aside.
Add the peeled and deveined shrimp to a small bowl along with olive oil and season with the listed spices. Mix well then set aside.
Bring a large pot of salted water to boil then cook bowtie pasta until al dente. Reserve 1/4 cup of pasta water.
In a large skillet, drizzle in olive oil and heat to medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook until golden brown 2-3 minutes per side.
Remove sausage from the pan and set aside. Add the seasoned shrimp, cook until browned on both sides. 2-3 minutes per side. Once fully cooked, remove and set aside.
Lastly, add a few drizzles of olive oil and cook the seasoned chicken until fully cooked. 3 minutes per side. Remove and set aside once done.
Add butter along with all the chopped veggies. Sautee for 1-2 minutes. Then add in garlic and stir until fragrant.
Add in heavy cream and bring to a light simmer. Slowly stir in all of the cheeses, reserving extra parmesan for garnish.
Once sauce is desired consistency, add in the cooked pasta and some pasta water.
Lightly season with additional cajun seasoning if desired then add back in the chopped protein, shrimp, chicken, and sausage.
Stir until everything is well combined then garnish with additional parmesan, cajun seasoning and green onions.
Serve and enjoy!
Cube up room temperature steak then add to a bowl along with olive oil and seasoning.
Mix well and let marinate for at least 20 minutes.
Heat a cast iron to medium-high heat along with butter and olive oil then add steak being sure not to overcrowd the pan.
Sear each side until charred or preferred doneness, 2-3 minutes per.
Once all the steak is cooked, plate with your favorite sides and pour chimichurri sauce over the bites or toss in sauce.
Enjoy!
Bring a medium sized pot of water to boil, generously salt.
Once boiling add cubed up and peeled potatoes into the water and boil until fork tender. About 25 minutes.
Strain then add the cooked potatoes to a bowl.
In a separate small saucepan, drizzle in truffle oil and then add in shallots and garlic. Sautee until fragrant, 2 minutes or so.
Add in cream and milk. Bring to a light simmer then remove from heat.
To the cooked potatoes, add salt, pepper and butter. Use a hand mixer to slightly break up the potatoes.
Add in half of the warm cream and continue to mix. Gradually add in the remaining cream and blend potatoes until desired consistency.
Garnish with additional pepper, parsley and a few pads of butter.
Serve and enjoy!
Using kitchen shears cut chicken breast into chunks/cubes.
Add to a bowl along with the listed ingredients and mix until well combined.
Let marinate for at least 20 minutes or up to overnight.
Then add 3-4 chicken chunks to small skewers.
Add the skewers to a greased air fryer and spray with cooking spray.
Air fry for 26 minutes, flipping every 8 minutes or so.
To a small saucepan add butter and garlic. Heat to medium heat and saute until fragrant then remove from heat.
To a bowl add garlic butter and all the listed ingredients mix until well combined.
Once all of the skewers are cooked, brush on garlic parmesan sauce and serve with your favorite sides!
Heat a wok to medium-high heat. Add oil then add in marinated chicken and sauteuntil thoroughly cooked.
Once cooked, set aside. Drizzle more oil and scramble in eggs. Once done, set aside.
Add onion and carrots, saute until translucent then add in ginger, saute for 1 minute then follow with garlic.
Add in gochujang and rice. Stir until well incorporated.
Add in hoisin, sesame oil, and a pinch of salt, stir.
Add in the cooked chicken, and eggs then soy sauce. Sauté until well combined.
Once rice is desired texture, remove from heat and garnish with green onions.
(Optional) drizzle on Japanese barbecue sauce.
Serve and enjoy!
In a medium size bowl add the chicken tenders and listed spices and ingredients.
Mix well, set aside and allow to marinate for at least 1 hour or up to overnight.
In a separate shallow bowl add flour and spices then whisk together, set aside.
Preheat large frying pot of oil to 360 degrees.
Remove the marinated tenders from the fridge then bring to room temperature. Add each one to the flour mixture and evenly coat then set onto a wire rack.
After 5-10 minutes or once your oil is heated, shake off excess flour and fry tenders until golden brown. 10-12 minutes.
Cook until all the tenders are done being sure not to overcrowd the frying pot.
Once cooked, add to a wire rack to cool, then brush on the barbecue sauec.
Garnish with sesame seeds and green onion.
Serve with cold ranch and enjoy!
Trim excess fat from steak and slice into even strips.
Add steak to a bowl along with the listed ingredients. Mix until well combined then set aside.
Whisk together the stir fry sauce ingredients then set aside.
Follow package directions to cook rice.
Add olive oil to a large pan over high heat. Allow the oil to heat (1-2 minutes) then add the beef in a single layer.
Cook untouched on both sides, 1-2 minutes per. Remove from the pan and set aside.
Deglaze with chicken stock then add in block florets. Stir then cover and allow to cook until bright green. 5 minutes or so.
Add the sauce and cooked beef back in. Add in a corn starch slurry to thicken (equal parts water and corn starch). Reduce heat to medium and allow the sauce to simmer and thicken.
Once desired thickness is achieved, remove from heat and serve.
Pair with white rice, garnish with green onions and sesame seeds, then serve and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: new york strip, cut into bite sized pieces

directions.Direction: In a small bowl, combine the steak bites and other listed ingredients. Mix well then set aside.
Heat oil and butter in a medium-sized cast iron on high heat.
Add steak in an even layer and cook for 2-3 minutes per side untouched in batches. Be sure not to overcrowd or overcook the steak. Remove once done.
Once all the steak is cooked, reduce heat to medium-low then add in butter and garlic. Allow to sauté for 1-2 minutes to become fragrant.
Add in sprigs of thyme and rosemary then add the steak back to the pan. Stir everything together until well combined for 2 minutes then remove from the pan and set aside.
To the same pan add in shallot, garlic, and black pepper. Sauté  for 1-2 minutes.
Deglaze the pan with white cooking wine. Then add cream and allow to simmer on medium heat for 3-4 minutes.
Add in pepper, more prime steak truffle seasoning, parsley, and drizzle in truffle oil. Taste and adjust for salt.
Once the sauce is thickened, or coats the back of a spoon it's done. Remove from the heat.
Lastly, plate steak over mashed potatoes and drizzle the peppercorn truffle sauce over top.
Serve and enjoy!

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: Garlic Butter Steak Bites & Truffle Peppercorn Sauce

directions.Direction: Cut chicken breast and thighs into even bite-sized pieces/ cubes. Add to a bowl and drizzle with olive oil, generally season, mix and then set aside.
Add shrimp to a small bowl, drizzle with olive oil, then season and set aside to marinade.
Slice sausage into small bite-sized pieces. Then add to a large cold pot and heat to medium heat.
Once the sausage is fully cooked, remove it and set aside. To the same pot, add butter and the seasoned shrimp. Cook the shrimp for 2 minutes per side then remove and set aside.
Add avocado oil to the pot and heat to medium-high heat. Add the seasoned chicken in an even layer and remove once fully cooked; about 10 minutes.
Add butter, peppers, onion, and celery. Cook until translucent (2-3 minutes). Then stir in garlic and cook until fragrant (1 minute).
Stir in tomato paste until well combined. Then add in the rice and toast for 1 minute.
Add in chicken broth, the cooked chicken, and sausage, then stir. Stir in more seasonings, 1-2 tsp each.
Top with bay leaves then cover. Bring to a rolling simmer then reduce heat to low and cook for 14-18 minutes.
After about 14 minutes, remove the lid and gently fluff the rice then top with the cooked shrimp.
Allow to cook for another 5 minutes then remove from heat and garnish with green onions.
Serve and enjoy!
Make the wonton filling. Combine all the listed ingredients in a bowl.
Prepare your wrapping station. Have a small bowl of water, the wonton wrappers, and the prepared filling.
Dip your finger in the water and moisten the edges of the wrapper. Use a butter knife to add about 1/2 a teaspoon of the filling into the center, then fold into a triangle.
Moisten one of the bottom corners with more water, then bring the two corners together, fold, and seal. Repeat until all wontons are wrapped.
Bring a medium-large pot of water to a boil and add wontons in batches. Cook for two minutes, then once they float, cook for an additional one minute.
Drain into a shallow bowl, then top with the chili oil sauce, green onion, and sesame seeds. Enjoy!
Carefully remove seeds from all of the chiles. Halve the tomatoes, and onions, then rough chop the garlic. Set aside once done.
Divide chuck roast into even chunks, then generously oil both the chuck roast and short rib. Generously season all sides until well coated.
In a dry, hot pan, add in chiles and whole spices. Toast for 1-2 minutes then remove and set aside.
Heat a large pan to medium-high heat, then add in oil. Once the pan is hot, sear the seasoned meat in batches until just browned about 2-3 minutes. Set aside.
Once all of the meat is cooked and removed, in the same pan, add in the listed ingredients.
Saute for 2-3 minutes. Then add in toasted chiles and whole spices. Add in water until all of the chilis are fully covered.
Bring up to a rapid simmer, cover, then reduce to low and allow chiles to soften. After about 15 minutes remove from heat.
Carefully add the softened chiles and vegetables to a blender or food processor along with 1 cup of the broth. Blend until smooth, and a pourable paste, in batches if needed.
Use a mesh strainer to strain the blended mixture into a medium bowl until ready to pour.
In a large pot or Dutch oven add  3 cups of water and the cooked beef. Heat to medium. Pour over the strained tomato and chile mixture from the previous step.
Add in the listed seasonings and then bring stew up to a high simmer, then reduce to low and cover. Let the stew cook for at least 3 hours.
At hour 3, remove the meat and shred it. (Optional) Strain the consome once more for an extra smooth stew.
Make sure to adjust the stew for salt, then add some of the consome to the shredded meat in a separate bowl.
Assemble tacos with a generous amount of shredded beef, queso oaxaca, onion and cilantro, and of course the delicious consome!
Dip the tortillas on both sides in the chile sauce (consome) then fry in a hot pan. Add in your favorite toppings and fry on both sides until brown and crispy.
Serve and enjoy!
Trim excess fat from steak, then cut into bite-sized cubes and add to a medium bowl or shallow dish.
Drizzle with olive oil, then generously season with the listed spice and truffle oil. Mix well and set aside
Heat a medium-large sized cast iron to medium-high heat. Then melt in butter and drizzle in olive oil.
Add in the seasoned steak bites in an even layer, making sure not to overcrowd. Sear for about 1 minute per side or until browned. Then remove from the pan and set aside.
Once all the steak is cooked and removed, set heat to medium-low then melt down butter and add in minced garlic. Saute garlic until fragrant (1 minute). Stir in thyme and rosemary.
Add the cooked steak back in and stir everything together until well coated in the garlic butter. 2-3 minutes. Remove steak and set aside.
Add in the minced shallot, garlic, and peppercorns. Stir and saute until fragrant, 2 minutes.
Deglaze the pan with white wine, and allow to simmer and reduce. 1-2 minutes.
Stir in heavy cream then drizzle in truffle oil, additional peppercorn, and season to taste.
Once the sauce is velvety, smooth, and coats the back of the spoon it's done. Garnish with parsley.
Pair your steak bites with your favorite sides, I chose creamy garlic mashed potatoes, and roasted asparagus. Drizzle the cream sauce on top of your steak bites and serve!

Creator: jordanramsy
Name: Garlic Steak Bites w/ Truffle Peppercorn Cream Sauce

ingredients.Name: chicken, divided into even chunks/ pieces

directions.Direction: To a large bowl, add the chicken pieces and chunks.
Add in the green seasoning and thyme.
Generously season with the listed spices. Then mix everything until evenly coated in the spices and green season. Note: I recommend using gloves as the curry can stain your nails.
Refrigerate overnight minimum or up to 48 hours for maximum flavor.
Remove lobster tail meat from the shell, reserving 1-2 lobster tails for garnish.
Then roughly chop the lobster meat into bite-sized chunks. Add into a small bowl, then season with the listed spices, mix, and set aside.
Bring a large pot of water to boil, add 2-3 pinches of salt, then add bucatini pasta, and cook until al dente.
Preheat a skillet to medium heat. Add in olive oil and melt in butter, then add in the seasoned lobster meat.
Saute for 5 minutes, then remove and set aside. In the same pan melt in butter.
Add in shallots and garlic, then stir constantly until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
Deglaze with white wine and cook down until slightly reduced by half, 2-3 minutes.
Stir in chicken stock and cream.
Add in tomatoes, then season with the listed spices. Bring cream to a high simmer, then reduce heat to low and stir in cheeses. 1/2 cup at a time, until fully melted.
Once the sauce is thick and creamy, stir in the cooked lobster and squeeze fresh lemon juice on top.
Then add in about 3 cups of the cooked bucatini pasta. Splash in 1-2 tbsp of pasta water as needed.
Stir together until everything is well combined. Taste and adjust for salt as needed.
Garnish the pasta with fresh chopped parsley, and freshly fine grated parmesan.
Serve and enjoy!
In a small bowl, combine the listed spices and oil until a paste/ marinade forms.
To the clean and dry lamb chops, lightly salt both sides. Then brush the seasoning paste on all sides. Set aside and allow to marinate for at least an hour.
Heat a cast iron skillet to medium-high heat, then add in oil and butter. Heat until lightly smoking.
Then add in lamb chops in batches. Cook for 3-5 minutes per side depending on temperature preference.
Then add in 2-3 sprigs of thyme, rosemary, shallot, and 4-6 cloves of crushed/ smashed garlic.
Reduce heat to low, then add in butter and baste lamb chops for about 3-5 minutes.

Add the cooked wings to a large sauce bowl, then cover in the honey garlic glaze. Toss until well coated.
Serve with ranch or bleu cheese and enjoy!
Spray about 15 tortillas with cooking spray and then wrap in paper towels. Heat in the microwave for 30 seconds.
Remove from the microwave and begin rolling the taquitos 1 by 1.
Add equal parts chicken and cheese to one end, roughly 1 tbsp each.
Seal the end with a cornstarch and water paste. Tightly roll and set aside.
Once all the taquitos are rolled, freeze for 5-10 minutes.
To a food processor or blender, add the last seven ingredients. Blend until smooth and refrigerate.
Remove the taquitos from the freezer and heat a large pan to medium heat with 1/2 cup of oil.
Add the taquitos and cook until golden brown and crispy.
Once all the taquitos are cooked, garnish with cilantro, avocado crema and pico de gallo, enjoy!

Name: Hot Chipotle Tacos
Description: The Best Recipe for Hot Chipotle Tacos

directions.Direction: To a large bowl, combine the chicken breast, chipotle puree, lime juice,  spices, and 1-2 tbsp of olive oil.
Mix well and refrigerate for 30 minutes or up to 24 hours.
Heat a large cast iron griddle or pan to medium-high heat with 1-2 tbsp of olive oil.
